jsa.TaskDescription: Drive to site and review flushing procedures
WaysToMitigate: Add secondary containment and spill remediation tools.
Cordon off area under which falling objects could occur.
Ensure that flammable substances are separated from the ignition source.
Lock-out, tag-out all sources of electricity.
Drink plenty of water and take frequent breaks.
Follow chemical handling procedures shown on SDS.
Remove slip/trip hazards prior to beginning work.
Understand the travel areas of moving objects and vehicles.
WaysToMitigateReport: Add secondary containment and spill remediation tools prior to beginning work.
Cordon off area under which falling objects could occur, and ensure that no one enters that area while the falling objects hazard exists.
Ensure that flammable substances are separated from the ignition source, or eliminate the ignition source altogether.

Lock-out / tag-out rotating equipment, or if machines are required to be operating, ensure that all moving parts are properly shrouded to prevent a human from touchingthe moving parts. (Each lock must have onlyone key, which is to be controlledexclusively by the employee.)
Drink plenty of water and take frequent breaks in cool shelters.
Follow chemical handling procedures shown on SDS.
Follow proper confined space procedures, including having a safety watch person at the entrance, and monitoring the air for breathability.
Properly isolate dangerously hot/cold objects so that they are untouchable by a human.
Remove slip/trip hazards prior to beginning work, or cordon off the area where slip/trip hazards are present.
Shut off all sources of electricity using proper lock-out, tag-out methods. (Each lockmust have only one key, which is to be controlled exclusively by the employee.)
Understand the travel areas of moving objects and vehicles and avoid those areas as necessary.
